  "metadata": {
    "what_it_measures": "Real Gross Domestic Product. BEA. Quarterly: Advance (~4 weeks after quarter-end), Second (2 months), Third (3 months).\n",
    "why_it_matters": "Baumohl #10. Mostly priced in by release, but composition (consumer vs. capex vs. inventory) drives sector rotation. Negative real GDP for 2 quarters = technical recession.\n",
    "scoring_rule": "Annualized growth rate: > 3% \u2192 +50 | 2-3% \u2192 +20 | 1-2% \u2192 0 | 0-1% \u2192 -30 | <0% \u2192 -80. Phase 3."
